post_text:
February 4, 2019 - Incident at the Caroline L. Reutter School.

Just before we were scheduled to start our school day, we were notified of a faint smell of natural gas in the exterior vicinity of the school. As a precautionary measure, we decided to evacuate the occupants of the school building and to keep the students on their buses.

The Franklinville Volunteer Fire Company, South Jersey Gas, and the Franklin Township Police Department responded to the school in order to investigate the reported situation. Upon investigation, there was no reported measurable amounts of natural gas within the interior or exterior of the school.

All students, faculty, and staff are safe and the school day has started with normal operations.

Just before we were scheduled to start our school day, we were notified of a faint smell of natural gas in the exterior vicinity of the school. As a precautionary measure, we decided to evacuate the occupants of the school building and to keep the students on their buses.

The Franklinville Volunteer Fire Company, South Jersey Gas, and the Franklin Township Police Department responded to the school in order to investigate the reported situation. Upon investigation, there was no reported measurable amounts of natural gas within the interior or exterior of the school.

All students, faculty, and staff are safe and the school day has started with normal operations.
